    "body": "### Problem\n\nFor example, a lsp-codelens that shows amount of references to a method, is shown on the same line as the function.\nIf you have a long method name, or if there are diagnostics on the same line, it might be quite hard to see.\nIf the method is folded, the virtual text for codelens dissapears.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCodelens could be shown on a separate line, i.e. above the function.\nCould be configurable. \nSimilarly done in other editors, and would avoid competing for real estate with other tools. ",
